1
00:01:10,480 --> 00:01:14,240
I want you two to stir up some chaos on this flight.

2
00:01:14,240 --> 00:01:16,920
Or better yet...cause a full-blown tragedy.

3
00:01:17,520 --> 00:01:19,720
Even if Madam Porn told you to trigger a tragedy,

4
00:01:19,720 --> 00:01:21,120
Don’t go killing anyone, alright?

5
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:24,240
Someone on this damn plane stole from me! They took my necklace!

6
00:01:24,240 --> 00:01:25,680
Please stay calm. Where did you last see it?

7
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:28,080
I’m giving you my ultimate move.

8
00:01:29,520 --> 00:01:30,520
So we'll blow up this plane?

9
00:01:32,520 --> 00:01:33,520
Fire!

10
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:36,800
This time, this airline is going to be doomed!

11
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:51,080
Isn’t Madam Porn celebrating Halloween a bit too early?

12
00:01:51,080 --> 00:01:52,840
Were you raised in a lavender field or something?

13
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:56,840
How is this even a celebration? One more step and it’ll be a full-blown witchcraft lair.

14
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:00,800
Siri, my face is over here.

15
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:04,560
Mom!

16
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:07,640
Mom is used to call...

17
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:08,640
a mother...

18
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:14,560
Aren’t you gonna turn on the lights, Madam?

19
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:17,840
Darkness suits me just fine.

20
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:19,480
Wait…did your electricity get cut off?

21
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:22,000
As if I’d be broke like you.

22
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:25,640
The darkness…it’s just like my soul.

23
00:02:25,640 --> 00:02:29,640
Because I’ve had to watch Glamorous Airline rise higher and higher, day after day.

24
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:32,760
But I don’t know how to investigate them anymore.

25
00:02:32,760 --> 00:02:36,160
Mr. Glam is nearly impossible to get close to.

26
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:38,280
You don’t need to investigate anymore.

27
00:02:38,280 --> 00:02:41,080
Put the Glam thing on hold.

28
00:02:41,080 --> 00:02:45,080
What I want you two to do now is...

29
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:48,800
Destroy Glamorous Airlines’ reputation.

30
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:50,240
You mean, like, spread fake news to ruin their image?

31
00:02:50,240 --> 00:02:51,280
No.

32
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:53,280
Nothing fake.

33
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:56,760
I want everyone to witness the undeniable truth...

34
00:02:56,760 --> 00:03:00,720
that airline is truly terrible.

35
00:03:00,720 --> 00:03:04,720
I want you two to stir up some chaos on this flight.

36
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:06,480
Damage their reputation.

37
00:03:06,480 --> 00:03:10,480
Or better yet...cause a full-blown tragedy.

38
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:17,480
Siri, stop doing that.

39
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:21,040
Yes, Madam.

40
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:35,800
Everyone looks normal enough.

41
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,800
Doesn't seem like anything's gonna happen on this flight.

42
00:03:47,840 --> 00:03:48,960
Ouch!

43
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:52,760
Hey! Why’d you bump into me? Watch where you're going!

44
00:03:52,760 --> 00:03:53,920
Ugh, look at your hat first, would you?

45
00:03:53,920 --> 00:03:56,600
How's anyone supposed to sit when you come in disturbing everyone like this?

46
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:57,760
Disturbing? How am I disturbing anyone?

47
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:01,200
What the hell are you even wearing?

48
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:04,600
You're a queen, why are you dressed like a boy?

49
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:06,080
It’s called Dawson, sweetie.

50
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:07,120
And what if it’s not?

51
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:08,880
Hey!

52
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:10,320
Look at your outfit first!

53
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:12,360
Your skirt’s huge, your head’s huge...

54
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:14,000
careful or you’ll bump into an iceberg!

55
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:17,640
Where? Where? Where?

56
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:20,560
Right here. Listen to your friend for once. What are you even wearing?

57
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:23,280
Hey, don’t insult my friend like that!

58
00:04:23,280 --> 00:04:25,120
You were just insulting your own friend a second ago!

59
00:04:25,120 --> 00:04:29,120
What? When? We were just chatting, nicely!

60
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:31,480
Yeah, just talking normal, man.

61
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:32,480
What's this?

62
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:34,680
People these days...

63
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:37,720
Miss! I'm going to Yasotorn.

64
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:39,720
They wouldn’t let me pick a seat.

65
00:04:46,760 --> 00:04:48,400
Still no plan, huh?

66
00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:49,480
No.

67
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:51,320
Everyone looks totally normal.

68
00:04:51,320 --> 00:04:52,520
Where are we sitting?

69
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:56,520
Look where you're going. I'm trying to find our seats.

70
00:04:58,080 --> 00:04:58,680
This one, right?

71
00:04:58,680 --> 00:04:59,280
Here, isn’t it?

72
00:04:59,280 --> 00:05:01,480
Then just go in already!

73
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:03,400
Why are you pushing me?

74
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:04,960
Because I get the aisle seat.

75
00:05:04,960 --> 00:05:07,040
Well, I couldn’t get the seat I wanted!

76
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:07,880
Excuse me, passengers.

77
00:05:07,880 --> 00:05:08,320
Yes?

78
00:05:08,320 --> 00:05:09,840
Please don’t fight.

79
00:05:09,840 --> 00:05:11,200
We’re not fighting.

80
00:05:11,200 --> 00:05:12,400
Tell her!

81
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:15,720
Tell her what? You already said it!

82
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:16,800
Does this count as a fight?

83
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:18,000
Nope.

84
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:20,680
Oh, okay. Well then, let’s keep not fighting, shall we?

85
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:21,680
Girlie!

86
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:24,560
Damn it!

87
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:27,320
This is called normal.

88
00:05:27,320 --> 00:05:31,320
So...what tragedy could even happen?

89
00:05:32,440 --> 00:05:33,440
I don't know. You tell me.

90
00:05:41,360 --> 00:05:42,360
What are you doing?

91
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:44,920
What I have to do.

92
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:55,080
Even if Madam Porn told you to start a tragedy,

93
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:56,080
don’t kill anyone, okay?

94
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:58,920
Stop moving, stay still.

95
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:04,360
You can’t do that.

96
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:10,280
It tickles!

97
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:15,560
What?

98
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:17,600
What are you two even playing at?

99
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:20,400
Freaking weirdos. People will start shipping you.

100
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:22,520
What murder are you even talking about?

101
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:23,880
You’re the only one murdering me here!

102
00:06:23,880 --> 00:06:26,080
You were about to choke a passenger!

103
00:06:26,080 --> 00:06:27,600
I was just trying to give this necklace back.

104
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:29,080
They dropped it when they boarded.

105
00:06:29,080 --> 00:06:32,760
Damn, I thought you were finally starting the chaos Madam Porn asked for.

106
00:06:32,760 --> 00:06:34,520
How the hell is one necklace gonna ruin everything?

107
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:38,520
A thief! There’s a thief on board!

108
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:40,920
Someone stole my necklace!

109
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:42,880
Could it be…this one?

110
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:43,440
Probably not.

111
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:45,640
Has anyone seen my friend’s necklace?

112
00:06:45,640 --> 00:06:47,240
Doesn’t everyone have a necklace these days?

113
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:50,040
It’s got a tiny teddy bear charm.

114
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:51,720
Well yeah, bears are trendy now.

115
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:54,920
One of the eyes is a bit wonky.

116
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:56,600
That’s just how bears look!

117
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:58,600
On the back, it’s engraved “Ae.”

118
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:01,760
Well, that’s oddly specific.

119
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:03,720
This is it, All-New!

120
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:07,160
Oh, no! No need to search anymore, I’ve been robbed for sure!

121
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:10,760
There’s a thief on this plane!

122
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:13,920
All-New, give it back now before this turns into something bigger.

123
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:14,440
Here!

124
00:07:14,440 --> 00:07:16,680
Yeah, I know. That’s her necklace. Return it already.

125
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:17,440
No.

126
00:07:17,440 --> 00:07:19,880
This is it. This is our chaos plan.

127
00:07:19,880 --> 00:07:22,240
We go along with it, pretend someone stole it.

128
00:07:22,240 --> 00:07:23,560
Add a couple more dramatic incidents.

129
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:25,400
Boom! Glamorous Airlines goes down.

130
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:29,400
But what exactly do you want me to do?

131
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:31,440
Listen to me.

132
00:07:31,440 --> 00:07:35,440
If we do this right, your debt’s gone, and this mission is done.

133
00:07:37,080 --> 00:07:41,080
All-New, I seriously don’t know what to cause anymore. We'll blow up this plane?

134
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:56,120
An explosion just happened!

135
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:58,160
Hey! What the hell just happened?

136
00:07:58,160 --> 00:07:59,280
Someone explain, now!

137
00:07:59,280 --> 00:08:00,680
What happened, Chai?

138
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:03,480
On such a chill and breezy day like this?

139
00:08:03,480 --> 00:08:05,360
Yeah, super chill...your face just got scorched!

140
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:08,880
Wait, “scorched”? It’s just the tan, okay?

141
00:08:08,880 --> 00:08:09,600
Exactly.

142
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:10,640
It’s called contouring.

143
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:11,800
What happened? Spit it out.

144
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:14,280
Umm…it’s called homeless couture.

145
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:17,920
From Amphoe Mueang, Tambon Na Mueang, in the country of Paris.

146
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:21,920
Enough! Just tell me what actually happened!

147
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:32,760
Flight staff! Where’s the flight staff?

148
00:08:32,760 --> 00:08:33,880
They’re called flight attendants.

149
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:34,760
Flight attendants?

150
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:36,560
Flight attendants! Where are they?

151
00:08:36,560 --> 00:08:37,520
Ouch! Don’t climb!

152
00:08:37,520 --> 00:08:38,520
I will climb!

153
00:08:39,680 --> 00:08:40,680
Well? How’d that go?

154
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:41,720
It hurts, obviously!

155
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:43,080
Told you not to climb.

156
00:08:43,680 --> 00:08:44,680
Well, I lost my necklace.

157
00:08:45,040 --> 00:08:46,040
Ugh, what an embarrassment!

158
00:08:47,560 --> 00:08:49,800
Don’t mind them, that’s just how they talk.

159
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:50,800
Not normal.

160
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:55,040
Excuse me, what seems to be the problem?

161
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:57,840
Can I ask you something? Do planes have thieves on board?

162
00:08:57,840 --> 00:08:59,360
Someone stole my necklace!

163
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:02,000
A thief? Okay, calm down, where did you lose it?

164
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:05,720
If I knew where I lost it, I’d have found it already!

165
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:07,360
Stupid! Probably didn’t even read any books at school!

166
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:09,200
So…is it the necklace or your book that’s missing?

167
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:13,200
Ugh, I’m calling you stupid, you dumb cow!

168
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:14,640
Tell her!

169
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:18,640
So you’re not gonna do anything about this? Fine!

170
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:21,200
So...you're saying you’re not pressing charges?

171
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:23,720
I’ll let social media deal with you.

172
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:29,080
Everyone, listen up! Glamorous Airline...

173
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:31,040
has a thief on board!

174
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:33,280
Our airline does not tolerate theft, ma’am.

175
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:35,360
We’ve been operating for years with high standards.

176
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:35,960
Look at her face! Look at it good!

177
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:36,720
Yes!

178
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:39,280
Tap the screen, everyone! Tap tap!

179
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:40,800
Feel free to share this!

180
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:42,400
Thank you for the stickers!

181
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:44,400
Thank you for the gifts!

182
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:45,640
Film this! Film it all!

183
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:46,240
There’s a thief!

184
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:49,760
Ma’am, I swear, there’s no thief!

185
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:51,760
Thank you, thank you for all the support!

186
00:09:51,760 --> 00:09:52,440
Thanks for the hearts! So sweet!

187
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:53,520
Hit share! Share it now!

188
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:54,680
Keep sharing, darlings!

189
00:09:54,680 --> 00:09:57,440
Thanks for the lovely fragrant roses!

190
00:09:57,440 --> 00:09:59,240
Film the flight attendant who looks like a man!

191
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:00,040
There’s no such person!

192
00:10:00,040 --> 00:10:00,680
See? They're not cooperating.

193
00:10:00,680 --> 00:10:01,720
Like and share, everyone!

194
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:02,880
Thank you for the heart me!

195
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:03,400
Thanks for the hearts!

196
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:04,080
Ice cream! Ice cream!

197
00:10:05,320 --> 00:10:06,320
How the hell are we supposed to start this?

198
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:09,200
Sugar.

199
00:10:09,520 --> 00:10:10,400
Salt.

200
00:10:10,400 --> 00:10:11,200
Fish sauce.

201
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:11,960
Pepper.

202
00:10:11,960 --> 00:10:13,960
Wow...none of this is useful at all.

203
00:10:21,520 --> 00:10:22,520
Laxatives?

204
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:25,040
Why the hell do we even have that?

205
00:10:26,640 --> 00:10:27,640
Wait.

206
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:28,760
What?

207
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:33,440
I think we’ve got a plan.

208
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:38,720
Actually, two plans!

209
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:40,480
What plans?

210
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:55,920
I'm shipping...

211
00:10:55,920 --> 00:10:57,240
you two...

212
00:10:57,240 --> 00:10:58,080
This makes me happy.

213
00:10:58,080 --> 00:10:59,240
They're serving some moments.

214
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:00,400
Cute.

215
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:01,280
Adorable.

216
00:11:01,280 --> 00:11:03,120
Chaba.

217
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:04,000
Yes?

218
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,160
Can you just not for a sec?

219
00:11:05,160 --> 00:11:06,160
Sure.

220
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:09,520
Passengers are freaking out, there’s yelling, something went missing!

221
00:11:09,520 --> 00:11:10,520
Move! Get out there, now!

222
00:11:23,400 --> 00:11:24,920
Ladies and gentlemen,

223
00:11:24,920 --> 00:11:27,680
There’s been a report of a missing item onboard.

224
00:11:27,680 --> 00:11:31,680
The crew kindly asks for your cooperation as we conduct a body search.

225
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:34,400
Please don’t panic.

226
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:35,080
No need to panic!

227
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:35,720
We appreciate your cooperation.

228
00:11:35,720 --> 00:11:36,720
We really appreciate your cooperation.

229
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:55,240
Chaba...

230
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:58,960
Can you please give this coffee to seat 12J?

231
00:11:58,960 --> 00:11:59,960
Yes, of course.

232
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:02,240
Coffee for you, sir.

233
00:12:02,440 --> 00:12:03,440
Thank you.

234
00:12:04,680 --> 00:12:06,680
Excuse me, may I check your bag?

235
00:12:16,080 --> 00:12:20,080
That’s suspicious, may I, please?

236
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:23,840
Is it over there?

237
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:26,200
This side?

238
00:12:27,040 --> 00:12:28,000
Here?

239
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:29,000
Is it this side?

240
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:30,240
That side?

241
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:32,600
Stay still! I said stay still!

242
00:12:39,520 --> 00:12:41,520
Excuse me, I need to use the bathroom.

243
00:12:45,840 --> 00:12:47,840
Please open the door, someone needs to use the toilet!

244
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:53,080
Open the door! Someone really needs to go!

245
00:12:53,880 --> 00:12:55,880
Open up! It’s urgent!

246
00:12:56,440 --> 00:12:59,040
I’m about to explode, it’s about to come out!

247
00:13:05,880 --> 00:13:07,320
Fire!

248
00:13:07,320 --> 00:13:09,640
Everyone, there’s a fire!

249
00:13:12,320 --> 00:13:14,280
It’s really on fire, Sky!

250
00:13:14,280 --> 00:13:16,120
Oh, no!

251
00:13:16,120 --> 00:13:16,520
Water! Get water!

252
00:13:16,520 --> 00:13:17,360
What do we do?

253
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:18,200
Water!

254
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:19,200
Quickly! It’s burning!

255
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:21,440
Is there any water?

256
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:23,800
All out. Everyone on this flight is super dehydrated.

257
00:13:23,800 --> 00:13:25,800
Bathroom! Get the bathroom!

258
00:13:28,760 --> 00:13:31,760
We can’t! It’s occupied! And we don’t know who's pooping!

259
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:35,000
What do we do?

260
00:13:36,560 --> 00:13:37,560
I’m ready. Open it.

261
00:13:38,640 --> 00:13:39,640
Sky, you open it now!

262
00:14:01,920 --> 00:14:04,440
Whoa...what a scene!

263
00:14:06,160 --> 00:14:07,920
Good thing no one got hurt.

264
00:14:07,920 --> 00:14:09,600
Well, we’re about to be.

265
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:11,280
Glamorous Airline is in serious trouble.

266
00:14:11,280 --> 00:14:13,760
After two famous influencers, Laurie and Ae...

267
00:14:13,760 --> 00:14:16,280
posted a viral video exposing the chaos on board…

268
00:14:16,280 --> 00:14:17,880
Let’s take a look.

269
00:14:17,880 --> 00:14:20,160
I hereby curse Glamorous Airline!

270
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:22,400
It is a terrible airline!

271
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:23,520
Umm...and who is this?

272
00:14:23,520 --> 00:14:25,760
That’s Laurie!

273
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:26,760
Laurie.

274
00:14:26,760 --> 00:14:28,960
Not only did they lose a passenger’s belongings...

275
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:30,280
But then...

276
00:14:30,280 --> 00:14:31,800
Who the hell is this one?

277
00:14:31,800 --> 00:14:33,080
Her name’s Ae.

278
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:34,120
Focus and watch properly.

279
00:14:34,120 --> 00:14:35,280
Okay.

280
00:14:35,280 --> 00:14:37,400
Just watch.

281
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:40,520
OH. MY. GOSH.

282
00:14:40,520 --> 00:14:43,360
Sir, you cannot just poop in the aisle.

283
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:45,120
Please put your pants back on!

284
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:48,760
See that? Not only was there an actual fire on the plane...

285
00:14:48,760 --> 00:14:51,840
but someone was pooping around!

286
00:14:51,840 --> 00:14:54,800
That’s right. Anyone thinking of flying with this airline...

287
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:56,200
Run! Don’t do it.

288
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:57,560
Next time, we’ll take you on a review of

289
00:14:57,560 --> 00:14:59,760
a way more fabulous airline.

290
00:14:59,760 --> 00:15:00,800
Seriously.

291
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:02,760
Don’t forget to follow our channel, Laurie…

292
00:15:02,760 --> 00:15:03,600
Ae.

293
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:04,840
No leaks, no stains.

294
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:06,600
Subscribe now to our channel:

295
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:07,400
Laurie

296
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:08,080
Ae’s...

297
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:09,600
Fast Wings Review!

298
00:15:09,600 --> 00:15:10,520
Quick and concise.

299
00:15:10,520 --> 00:15:13,840
No dragging.

300
00:15:13,840 --> 00:15:14,640
No smudging.

301
00:15:14,640 --> 00:15:15,200
No mess.

302
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:16,000
No stress.

303
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:17,880
And that’s all from us today, folks.

304
00:15:17,880 --> 00:15:19,640
We’ll see you next time, let’s see where we’ll be reviewing next!

305
00:15:19,640 --> 00:15:20,400
That’s all from us for now.

306
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:22,360
Don’t forget to like, share, and subscribe to our channel.

307
00:15:22,360 --> 00:15:22,960
Yes, that’s right

308
00:15:22,960 --> 00:15:23,920
We’re heading out now, everyone.

309
00:15:23,920 --> 00:15:24,200
Bye-bye.

310
00:15:24,480 --> 00:15:25,480
Bye-bye.

311
00:15:27,880 --> 00:15:31,000
These two are huge influencers. Millions of followers.

312
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:34,120
And now, this clip has gone completely viral.

313
00:15:34,120 --> 00:15:36,320
Someone needs to take responsibility.

314
00:15:36,320 --> 00:15:38,320
Everyone who was involved, take your positions.

315
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:49,160
Sky, you were the last one to use the microwave.

316
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:58,080
Chaba, you served coffee to the passenger who got food poisoning.

317
00:15:58,200 --> 00:16:02,200
And All-New, you told them to open the microwave lid...

318
00:16:03,440 --> 00:16:05,440
which caused the explosion.

319
00:16:08,440 --> 00:16:10,360
And Kreetha…

320
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:16,360
the whole time this was happening, you were locked in the lavatory and didn’t help anyone.

321
00:16:17,040 --> 00:16:19,040
The passengers couldn't get into the restroom.

322
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:27,480
So it’s clear. The chaos today was caused by…

323
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:39,240
Sky. Chaba.

324
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:40,360
Knew it! What a relief!

325
00:16:40,360 --> 00:16:41,360
Huh?

326
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:45,240
What about Kreetha? He was hogging the toilet the whole time!

327
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:48,680
I think he had diarrhea just like that passenger, right?

328
00:16:48,680 --> 00:16:51,080
Uh, yeah.

329
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:53,360
Why are we getting blamed then?

330
00:16:53,360 --> 00:16:57,000
Because you two have been flying longer, you should know better.

331
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:58,960
That’s because you look older.

332
00:16:58,960 --> 00:17:00,040
What the hell...

333
00:17:00,040 --> 00:17:04,040
Listen, you're still older than everyone else here combined.

334
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:07,080
Chai, technically Sky has worked here longer than me.

335
00:17:07,080 --> 00:17:08,920
She’s more experienced.

336
00:17:08,920 --> 00:17:11,280
I joined the company two seconds before you did.

337
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:12,240
Oh, yeah? Well, doesn't that mean you joined before I did?

338
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:15,040
So you wanted to be a junior now suddenly?

339
00:17:15,040 --> 00:17:17,560
Then resign right now so you’ll officially have less experience.

340
00:17:17,560 --> 00:17:19,040
Alright, alright.

341
00:17:19,040 --> 00:17:20,760
I’m not here to punish anyone.

342
00:17:20,760 --> 00:17:22,520
I just want to remind everyone...

343
00:17:22,520 --> 00:17:23,760
no matter who started flying first,

344
00:17:23,760 --> 00:17:25,000
or how long you’ve been here,

345
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:27,960
things can go wrong because of...

346
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:29,160
her!

347
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:29,720
You!

348
00:17:29,720 --> 00:17:30,040
No, you!

349
00:17:30,320 --> 00:17:30,840
No, you!

350
00:17:31,320 --> 00:17:32,320
Girl, you were so careless.

351
00:17:32,320 --> 00:17:35,520
Just look at the blast damage near your hair roots, it's obviously you.

352
00:17:35,520 --> 00:17:36,600
Wanna fight me, huh?

353
00:17:37,520 --> 00:17:38,120
Ugh, it’s always you.

354
00:17:38,120 --> 00:17:39,200
You're the one!

355
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:40,680
Are you on heat or what?

356
00:17:40,680 --> 00:17:42,280
It’s the same every time!

357
00:17:42,280 --> 00:17:43,280
Damn it.

358
00:17:43,960 --> 00:17:44,960
I’m not scared of you!

359
00:17:52,160 --> 00:17:53,440
What is it?

360
00:17:53,440 --> 00:17:54,280
What's going on?

361
00:17:54,280 --> 00:17:57,440
Sir, you cannot just poop in the aisle.

362
00:17:57,720 --> 00:17:58,560
See that?

363
00:17:58,560 --> 00:18:01,800
Not only was there an actual fire on the plane...

364
00:18:01,800 --> 00:18:04,800
but someone was pooping around!

365
00:18:04,800 --> 00:18:07,800
That’s right. Anyone thinking of flying with this airline...

366
00:18:07,800 --> 00:18:09,320
Run! Don’t do it.

367
00:18:09,320 --> 00:18:12,080
If Glamorous Airline doesn’t do something soon to fix their public image,

368
00:18:12,080 --> 00:18:14,960
this whole thing will crash and burn.

369
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:15,960
Let’s move on to our next report.

370
00:18:17,040 --> 00:18:19,840
Great job, All-New. Kreetha.

371
00:18:19,840 --> 00:18:21,960
That means...we did it.

372
00:18:21,960 --> 00:18:25,640
Yes. Phase one is complete.

373
00:18:25,640 --> 00:18:28,600
Now we move to phase two.

374
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:31,520
But Madam, even at this point, Glamorous Airline’s reputation is already ruined.

375
00:18:31,520 --> 00:18:32,960
Yeah, but it’s not completely dead yet.

376
00:18:32,960 --> 00:18:36,960
I want to make sure Glamorous Airline is destroyed beyond repair.

377
00:18:37,280 --> 00:18:39,280
I won’t stop until it’s buried.

378
00:18:40,960 --> 00:18:46,400
That’s why this time, I’m giving you the ultimate weapon...

379
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:49,200
to end this game for good.

380
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:51,520
Siri, bring that thing.

381
00:18:51,520 --> 00:18:52,520
Yes, Madam.

382
00:18:54,040 --> 00:18:57,520
No, not that thing. I mean that thing.

383
00:18:57,520 --> 00:18:58,520
Ohh.

384
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:03,360
Ugh, not this!

385
00:19:03,360 --> 00:19:04,120
Go back! Go back!

386
00:19:04,120 --> 00:19:06,120
I meant the thing in the box.

387
00:19:06,120 --> 00:19:08,120
Oh! That thing.

388
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:29,040
Sky, you know why

389
00:19:30,400 --> 00:19:33,120
you’re in this room right now, don’t you?

390
00:19:33,120 --> 00:19:34,360
Because of that Chaba.

391
00:19:34,360 --> 00:19:36,480
I told you already...

392
00:19:36,480 --> 00:19:37,920
I don’t want you two fighting.

393
00:19:37,920 --> 00:19:40,000
She’s a fake.

394
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:42,000
That kind of performance...

395
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:44,680
the audience can see right through it.

396
00:19:44,680 --> 00:19:46,960
The real monster...

397
00:19:46,960 --> 00:19:48,200
is Chaba.

398
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:49,960
Don’t get too emotional, Sky.

399
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:52,160
Don’t go too deep.

400
00:19:54,080 --> 00:19:56,640
I won’t fly anymore...

401
00:19:56,640 --> 00:19:58,880
if you still don’t believe that Chaba is a monster.

402
00:19:58,880 --> 00:20:00,040
Focus. Focus.

403
00:20:00,040 --> 00:20:01,040
I'm focusing right now, okay?

404
00:20:04,040 --> 00:20:05,720
If you want to play this game...

405
00:20:05,720 --> 00:20:09,760
you have to use this...this...

406
00:20:09,760 --> 00:20:11,200
not this.

407
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:14,520
What you need to do now...

408
00:20:14,520 --> 00:20:16,640
is go back and fly...

409
00:20:16,640 --> 00:20:20,080
and prove to everyone that you are the real Glamorous Airline crew.

410
00:20:21,680 --> 00:20:22,680
Can you do that?

411
00:20:24,720 --> 00:20:25,720
Yes.

412
00:20:26,800 --> 00:20:27,800
Very good.

413
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:31,760
And what you need to do...

414
00:20:31,760 --> 00:20:33,760
is bow down.

415
00:20:37,760 --> 00:20:38,760
Miss Ae...

416
00:20:39,360 --> 00:20:40,360
Miss Laurie...

417
00:20:41,720 --> 00:20:43,160
May I have another chance?

418
00:20:44,560 --> 00:20:45,920
I will do my very best.

419
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:49,120
Please let me prove myself one more time.

420
00:20:49,120 --> 00:20:50,120
May I?

421
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:51,480
Yes.

422
00:20:52,600 --> 00:20:54,240
If you ask me to fly,

423
00:20:54,240 --> 00:20:57,240
I’ll ask how high.

424
00:20:57,240 --> 00:20:59,000
If you ask me to serve,

425
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:01,840
I’ll ask which pose.

426
00:21:02,360 --> 00:21:05,040
You have to fight even harder now.

427
00:21:05,280 --> 00:21:06,280
Fighter.

428
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:11,080
I’ve been fighting since day one. And even now, I still have to fight.

429
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:15,080
And I’ll keep fighting.

430
00:21:15,080 --> 00:21:16,080
Strong.

431
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:17,400
Strong.

432
00:21:17,720 --> 00:21:18,720
Strong.

433
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:34,000
Moody’s Born to Be Brutal, today we’re here with Miss Chaba.

434
00:21:34,440 --> 00:21:37,240
There are so many questions people at home are dying to know.

435
00:21:37,240 --> 00:21:40,560
Are you ready to answer them all today?

436
00:21:40,560 --> 00:21:43,520
If I weren’t ready, I wouldn’t be here, right?

437
00:21:43,520 --> 00:21:47,520
Some people say you did it because you were jealous of Sky.

438
00:21:48,840 --> 00:21:51,960
Me? Jealous of Sky?

439
00:21:51,960 --> 00:21:54,920
I’m a flight attendant. I’ve got money.

440
00:21:54,920 --> 00:21:55,920
A career.

441
00:21:55,920 --> 00:21:56,920
Responsibilities.

442
00:21:56,920 --> 00:21:58,680
Just look at my body.

443
00:21:58,680 --> 00:22:00,200
I eat well, I sleep well.

444
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:01,760
Why would I be jealous of someone

445
00:22:01,760 --> 00:22:05,080
who still has to make monthly payments...on a mousepad?

446
00:22:05,080 --> 00:22:06,600
Honestly, with that face,

447
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:08,880
she probably shouldn’t even be allowed near a computer.

448
00:22:08,880 --> 00:22:12,880
Some people say you’re too fat to be a flight attendant.

449
00:22:13,720 --> 00:22:15,880
If someone hates me that much,

450
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:19,880
and all they can insult is my weight, I’d say that’s actually a win, right?

451
00:22:23,480 --> 00:22:25,560
You seem confident.

452
00:22:25,560 --> 00:22:31,440
So you’re saying the disaster on the last flight, it wasn’t you?

453
00:22:31,440 --> 00:22:34,400
I’m so tired of these nonsense rumors.

454
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:37,040
Like, please use your brain.

455
00:22:37,040 --> 00:22:39,600
Stop being so dumb. I’m exhausted.

456
00:22:41,560 --> 00:22:45,560
So what will you do about the people who say it was you?

457
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:49,120
Let me guess, must’ve been Sky, right?

458
00:22:49,120 --> 00:22:52,600
Next time, if you’ve got something to say, say it to my face.

459
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:54,600
Don’t go whispering behind my back.

460
00:22:54,600 --> 00:22:56,760
That’s just not cool.

461
00:22:56,760 --> 00:22:58,680
People can tell when someone’s faking it.

462
00:22:59,880 --> 00:23:03,640
And why do you think Sky did what she did?

463
00:23:03,640 --> 00:23:05,360
She wanted to make me look like the villain.

464
00:23:05,360 --> 00:23:07,360
But really, it was her the whole time.

465
00:23:09,040 --> 00:23:12,960
How about this...you fly this flight again.

466
00:23:12,960 --> 00:23:16,120
We’ve already sent tickets to Miss Ae and Miss Laurie.

467
00:23:16,120 --> 00:23:20,440
Go prove that your airline is fabulous.

468
00:23:20,720 --> 00:23:24,520
And that you are a fabulous flight attendant.

469
00:23:24,520 --> 00:23:28,960
Sounds perfect. If Sky finds out, she’ll probably die from heartbreak.

470
00:23:29,080 --> 00:23:32,440
Knowing the airline chose me to save the reputation.

471
00:23:33,480 --> 00:23:35,400
Are you flying to get revenge?

472
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:36,880
Let’s not call it revenge.

473
00:23:36,880 --> 00:23:40,280
Let’s call it...personal satisfaction.

474
00:23:40,280 --> 00:23:43,920
I know it’s probably wrong...but oh well.

475
00:23:43,920 --> 00:23:46,360
Alright then, fly this flight.

476
00:23:46,360 --> 00:23:50,760
And let our beloved Thai passengers decide.

477
00:23:51,520 --> 00:23:52,520
Deal.

478
00:24:13,840 --> 00:24:14,840
I’m not flying anymore.

479
00:24:16,320 --> 00:24:17,760
What?

480
00:24:18,920 --> 00:24:19,920
I’m not flying today.

481
00:24:20,320 --> 00:24:21,560
Wait, Sky!

482
00:24:21,560 --> 00:24:23,040
Chaba, don’t go yet!

483
00:24:23,040 --> 00:24:24,120
I’m not flying with her.

484
00:24:24,120 --> 00:24:26,320
Well, you didn’t tell me I had to fly with her!

485
00:24:26,880 --> 00:24:27,880
Hold on.

486
00:24:29,720 --> 00:24:33,360
Tid-Gift, I told you to calm Chaba down and you couldn’t even do that? Useless.

487
00:24:33,360 --> 00:24:35,840
You’re just as useless, Chai. Sky’s leaving too.

488
00:24:35,840 --> 00:24:36,160
What the hell?

489
00:24:36,520 --> 00:24:37,000
What the hell?

490
00:24:37,440 --> 00:24:38,440
You want a piece of me?

491
00:24:39,640 --> 00:24:42,680
Wait, wait, wait!

492
00:24:42,680 --> 00:24:44,560
Alright, fine! I’ll fly, okay?

493
00:24:44,560 --> 00:24:46,760
Right, I'll do it.

494
00:24:49,560 --> 00:24:50,560
Chaba, let’s go!

495
00:24:50,880 --> 00:24:51,880
I’ve got my eye on you, Tid-Gift.

496
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:54,360
That’s enough. Can you stop fighting already?

497
00:24:54,760 --> 00:24:55,720
Yeah.

498
00:24:55,720 --> 00:24:57,160
And don’t let me catch you two slapping each other again.

499
00:24:58,480 --> 00:24:59,480
Hey!

500
00:25:06,680 --> 00:25:07,680
Finally.

501
00:25:10,360 --> 00:25:12,000
And we didn’t even rehearse!

502
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:12,880
Brilliant.

503
00:25:12,880 --> 00:25:15,440
I almost missed the cue. It was brilliant!

504
00:25:16,720 --> 00:25:17,720
Thanks for the compliment.

505
00:25:17,720 --> 00:25:19,720
I was complimenting myself, thank you.

506
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:26,480
Of course you were. Only you would praise yourself. Impressive.

507
00:25:26,480 --> 00:25:28,200
Obviously.

508
00:25:29,320 --> 00:25:32,760
I love it when you're straightforward.

509
00:25:35,400 --> 00:25:36,400
I’m out.

510
00:25:44,360 --> 00:25:47,160
Tid-Gift, what the hell?

511
00:25:48,640 --> 00:25:49,640
I got chills.

512
00:25:52,800 --> 00:25:53,800
Hurry up and get in!

513
00:25:59,960 --> 00:26:02,040
What’s this box, All-New?

514
00:26:02,040 --> 00:26:03,040
I have no idea.

515
00:26:03,280 --> 00:26:05,000
But it got through airport security, so...

516
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:06,280
Probably nothing dangerous, right?

517
00:26:06,280 --> 00:26:08,520
Madam Porn said this is the game-ending move, bro.

518
00:26:10,200 --> 00:26:11,200
Then let’s open it.

519
00:26:12,280 --> 00:26:14,400
Why are you following me, huh?

520
00:26:14,400 --> 00:26:16,400
Who’s following you? You just walked into my path.

521
00:26:19,280 --> 00:26:22,240
Oh, I ship them. So cute.

522
00:26:22,240 --> 00:26:25,080
Ship what? They’re just friends.

523
00:26:25,080 --> 00:26:26,600
Tell that to yourself.

524
00:26:27,840 --> 00:26:28,840
Screw you!

525
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:31,000
Hey!

526
00:26:31,360 --> 00:26:32,360
Wait.

527
00:26:32,440 --> 00:26:32,640
Shit!

528
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:33,800
Shit!

529
00:26:38,240 --> 00:26:39,240
It’s...a scented sachet?

530
00:26:40,520 --> 00:26:41,760
Yeah, what’s with the screaming?

531
00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:44,600
Oh, nothing. No big deal.

532
00:26:46,760 --> 00:26:49,600
Actually, this might be good. Let’s keep it in the plane.

533
00:26:49,600 --> 00:26:50,960
In case another passenger farts.

534
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:51,920
It smells nice though.

535
00:26:52,040 --> 00:26:53,600
But why would Madam Porn give us a sachet?

536
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:56,360
Maybe Siri brought the wrong box?

537
00:26:57,360 --> 00:26:59,360
Oh, Thank God.

538
00:26:59,760 --> 00:27:01,400
If more drama keeps happening,

539
00:27:01,400 --> 00:27:03,400
Sky and Chaba are gonna get fired for sure.

540
00:27:07,520 --> 00:27:09,520
Why do you care so much about those two?

541
00:27:10,560 --> 00:27:12,560
Don’t forget whose side you’re on.

542
00:27:22,480 --> 00:27:25,200
Welcome aboard, our VVIP passengers.

543
00:27:25,720 --> 00:27:28,720
Hello.

544
00:27:29,960 --> 00:27:31,560
Hello.

545
00:27:33,600 --> 00:27:35,320
Hello.

546
00:27:40,640 --> 00:27:44,640
No need to worry, there definitely won’t be any drama like on the last flight.

547
00:27:45,080 --> 00:27:47,640
Don’t worry, with Chaba here, you’re in good hands.

548
00:27:47,640 --> 00:27:50,640
Please take your seats, please take your seats.

549
00:27:52,040 --> 00:27:54,160
I’ll personally take care of Miss Laurie and Miss Ae.

550
00:27:54,160 --> 00:27:59,160
It’s Chaba, spelled C-H-A-B-A, in case you’re planning to write a review or something.

551
00:27:59,160 --> 00:28:01,800
Yes, it’s Chaba.

552
00:28:01,800 --> 00:28:04,360
So you can spell her name right when you file a complaint.

553
00:28:11,960 --> 00:28:15,960
Here you go, just a small gift from our airline.

554
00:28:15,960 --> 00:28:19,960
Better to sip some mineral water from the Khao Khitchakut mountains, right?

555
00:28:20,120 --> 00:28:21,800
Here you go, mineral water. Drink up.

556
00:28:21,800 --> 00:28:24,440
These flowers were specially selected,

557
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:28,000
and turned into high-end fragrance imported straight from France.

558
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:30,920
But drinking mineral water is good for your throat...

559
00:28:30,920 --> 00:28:33,520
Why not hydrate first before your throat gets dry?

560
00:28:35,000 --> 00:28:37,760
Now try smelling this. Does it smell nice? Try it.

561
00:28:39,480 --> 00:28:41,560
Oh, right, you’re wearing a mask.

562
00:28:41,560 --> 00:28:44,120
Can you hold this for a second? I’ll take it off for you.

563
00:28:44,120 --> 00:28:46,120
I’m great at taking things off, stuff like that.

564
00:28:48,720 --> 00:28:49,720
So dumb.

565
00:28:50,360 --> 00:28:51,520
Can’t even take off a mask.

566
00:28:51,520 --> 00:28:51,920
Here.

567
00:28:51,920 --> 00:28:52,240
If you’re so good, you take it off.

568
00:28:52,240 --> 00:28:54,840
I’ll help you take it off. I will help.

569
00:28:59,240 --> 00:29:00,440
You’re just as dumb, honestly.

570
00:29:00,840 --> 00:29:01,880
What?

571
00:29:01,880 --> 00:29:02,440
It’s a deep feeling.

572
00:29:02,440 --> 00:29:03,440
I went to a school in the city.

573
00:29:03,440 --> 00:29:05,080
I went to a temple school. We learned about morality.

574
00:29:05,080 --> 00:29:06,600
What does that have to do with taking off a mask?

575
00:29:06,600 --> 00:29:08,000
You can’t take it off. You’re incompetent.

576
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:09,200
You shouldn’t even be a flight attendant.

577
00:29:09,200 --> 00:29:10,080
When exactly are you taking it off?

578
00:29:10,080 --> 00:29:11,240
I’m trying!

579
00:29:11,240 --> 00:29:12,360
I’m trying too!

580
00:29:12,360 --> 00:29:13,640
Look, it’s starting to loosen.

581
00:29:13,640 --> 00:29:14,640
Her wig’s slipping.

582
00:29:15,760 --> 00:29:17,760
Shouldn’t we stop them, All-New?

583
00:29:19,040 --> 00:29:21,360
No. Let them fight.

584
00:29:21,360 --> 00:29:23,760
This time, it’s gonna get messy.

585
00:29:25,640 --> 00:29:26,640
It's off!

586
00:29:27,040 --> 00:29:28,320
C-H-A-B-A.

587
00:29:28,320 --> 00:29:30,680
Write that in your review. Did I do well?

588
00:29:30,680 --> 00:29:33,880
How was that? I took it off without hurting you, right?

589
00:29:33,880 --> 00:29:39,080
Miss Ae still looks flawless and elegant, like a princess.

590
00:29:39,080 --> 00:29:39,720
Thank you.

591
00:29:39,720 --> 00:29:40,280
You’re welcome.

592
00:29:40,280 --> 00:29:44,120
But Miss Laurie...she’s so poised.

593
00:29:44,120 --> 00:29:46,200
Such a refined figure and waistline…

594
00:29:46,200 --> 00:29:48,200
You must be a socialite, right?

595
00:29:57,720 --> 00:29:59,840
Wait, King Kong’s allowed to fly now?

596
00:30:02,240 --> 00:30:06,240
Which King Kong? This is Pangkung and James.

597
00:30:07,280 --> 00:30:08,640
More like a palm weevil grub.

598
00:30:11,480 --> 00:30:13,480
What’s going on with her?

599
00:30:14,920 --> 00:30:16,920
What’s wrong with you?

600
00:30:18,200 --> 00:30:19,200
What is it?

601
00:30:35,360 --> 00:30:36,360
What’s happening right now?

602
00:30:38,240 --> 00:30:39,640
Could it be because...

603
00:31:01,800 --> 00:31:03,800
What’s inside the box, Madam?

604
00:31:03,800 --> 00:31:05,680
A scented sachet.

605
00:31:05,680 --> 00:31:07,400
I knew it!

606
00:31:07,400 --> 00:31:08,960
Huh? A scented sachet?

607
00:31:08,960 --> 00:31:11,240
But it’s not just any ordinary sachet.

608
00:31:11,240 --> 00:31:14,200
Because inside...is an herb

609
00:31:14,200 --> 00:31:18,680
that drives anyone who smells it completely insane.

610
00:31:20,360 --> 00:31:25,360
Now imagine, if the whole plane was full of crazy people, what would happen?

611
00:31:31,200 --> 00:31:32,200
Are you high, Madam?

612
00:31:37,640 --> 00:31:38,640
Siri!

613
00:31:39,160 --> 00:31:40,160
I’m sorry, Madam.

614
00:31:40,440 --> 00:31:41,440
I’m sorry.

615
00:31:41,440 --> 00:31:42,400
Will you do it again?

616
00:31:42,400 --> 00:31:43,120
No, Madam.

617
00:31:43,120 --> 00:31:43,800
Will you do it again?

618
00:31:43,800 --> 00:31:44,800
No, Madam.

619
00:31:55,120 --> 00:31:57,800
Would you prefer warm water or cold water, sir?

620
00:31:57,920 --> 00:31:59,920
Would you like to wash your face? You look a little messy.

621
00:32:00,080 --> 00:32:02,560
Hey! The Olympics are next year, you know!

622
00:32:02,560 --> 00:32:04,560
Go win that medal, come on!

623
00:32:04,560 --> 00:32:05,560
Yeah, let’s go!

624
00:32:11,080 --> 00:32:12,080
I’m not hurt.

625
00:32:15,880 --> 00:32:18,480
My dearest friend, Sky.

626
00:32:18,920 --> 00:32:20,520
This is Kreetha.

627
00:32:20,520 --> 00:32:23,240
Kreetha from Glamorous.

628
00:32:23,240 --> 00:32:27,840
No, I’m actually a spy.

629
00:32:28,440 --> 00:32:32,440
From Porn Airline.

630
00:32:34,240 --> 00:32:35,240
Undercover agent.

631
00:32:35,440 --> 00:32:36,080
Yes.

632
00:32:36,080 --> 00:32:37,080
Cobra.

633
00:32:37,280 --> 00:32:38,320
Yes.

634
00:32:38,320 --> 00:32:39,320
A mole.

635
00:32:39,920 --> 00:32:40,920
Yes.

636
00:32:41,360 --> 00:32:42,360
Salty filling.

637
00:32:42,880 --> 00:32:43,880
Correct.

638
00:32:44,400 --> 00:32:45,400
Sweet filling.

639
00:32:46,240 --> 00:32:47,240
Yes.

640
00:32:47,760 --> 00:32:48,760
Pala-U.

641
00:32:49,400 --> 00:32:50,400
Yes.

642
00:32:50,520 --> 00:32:51,520
Come on, hurry!

643
00:32:54,280 --> 00:32:55,280
Faster, faster!

644
00:33:12,840 --> 00:33:14,840
Everyone, get over here now!

645
00:33:16,360 --> 00:33:18,360
The review’s out! The review’s out!

646
00:33:18,960 --> 00:33:20,160
Hello, hello!

647
00:33:20,160 --> 00:33:21,720
You’re here with us...

648
00:33:21,720 --> 00:33:22,800
Laurie

649
00:33:22,800 --> 00:33:23,960
Ae

650
00:33:23,960 --> 00:33:25,000
With our channel, Fast Wings Review!

651
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:25,880
Quick and concise.

652
00:33:25,880 --> 00:33:26,840
No dragging.

653
00:33:26,840 --> 00:33:27,520
No smudging.

654
00:33:27,520 --> 00:33:28,200
No mess.

655
00:33:28,200 --> 00:33:29,040
No stress.

656
00:33:30,080 --> 00:33:31,440
I hate the slogan.

657
00:33:31,440 --> 00:33:32,440
And the name.

658
00:33:32,440 --> 00:33:33,800
I hate everything about this channel.

659
00:33:34,320 --> 00:33:38,320
Today, we’re back with Glamorous Airline again.

660
00:33:38,600 --> 00:33:40,800
And let us tell you, the service was amazing.

661
00:33:40,800 --> 00:33:41,640
So good.

662
00:33:41,640 --> 00:33:42,880
At one point, I was up there

663
00:33:42,880 --> 00:33:45,080
and I felt like I was floating in a dream.

664
00:33:45,080 --> 00:33:45,640
Really?

665
00:33:45,640 --> 00:33:48,840
Like drifting through the clouds.

666
00:33:48,840 --> 00:33:51,240
Oh my god, yes! I remember having so much fun

667
00:33:51,240 --> 00:33:52,720
and then suddenly I woke up

668
00:33:52,720 --> 00:33:54,400
and my necklace was back!

669
00:33:54,400 --> 00:33:58,240
Look, look, my necklace is here!

670
00:33:58,240 --> 00:34:00,080
For anyone still on the fence,

671
00:34:00,080 --> 00:34:02,280
try flying with them, and you’ll love it

672
00:34:02,280 --> 00:34:04,440
just like the two of us do!

673
00:34:04,440 --> 00:34:06,360
Yes! And wherever we fly next,

674
00:34:06,360 --> 00:34:09,840
it’ll definitely be with Glamorous Airline.

675
00:34:09,840 --> 00:34:11,760
Absolutely.

676
00:34:11,760 --> 00:34:13,440
We’ll say goodbye for now.

677
00:34:13,440 --> 00:34:14,800
Don’t forget to share,

678
00:34:14,800 --> 00:34:15,560
like,

679
00:34:15,560 --> 00:34:17,400
and subscribe!

680
00:34:17,400 --> 00:34:18,800
That’s all from us for today.

681
00:34:18,800 --> 00:34:19,800
Goodbye!

682
00:34:20,880 --> 00:34:22,760
They really meant it.

683
00:34:22,760 --> 00:34:24,160
They did.

684
00:34:24,160 --> 00:34:25,160
No sarcasm at all.

685
00:34:25,160 --> 00:34:26,160
Nope.

686
00:34:26,720 --> 00:34:29,720
Now everyone’s rushing to book with our airline.

687
00:34:29,720 --> 00:34:31,480
All flights are nearly full.

688
00:34:31,480 --> 00:34:32,760
We’re not getting laid off anymore.

689
00:34:36,160 --> 00:34:38,720
I don’t even know what happened

690
00:34:38,720 --> 00:34:40,880
that turned things around like this…

691
00:34:40,880 --> 00:34:42,320
If not for...

692
00:34:42,320 --> 00:34:44,160
Thank you.

693
00:34:49,080 --> 00:34:50,960
Thank you for what? He meant me.

694
00:34:50,960 --> 00:34:52,440
More like me, thank you.

695
00:34:52,440 --> 00:34:54,560
He was talking to both of you.

696
00:34:54,560 --> 00:34:55,960
No.

697
00:34:55,960 --> 00:34:57,720
I meant myself.

698
00:34:57,720 --> 00:34:59,160
If it wasn’t for me,

699
00:34:59,160 --> 00:35:02,400
none of this would have gone so well.

700
00:35:02,400 --> 00:35:03,400
Ugh.

701
00:35:04,040 --> 00:35:05,760
It’s because of me.

702
00:35:05,760 --> 00:35:07,520
Because I am the real flight attendant.

703
00:35:07,520 --> 00:35:08,800
So what, I’m fake now?

704
00:35:08,800 --> 00:35:09,960
Flight attendants are supposed to be good, aren’t they?

705
00:35:09,960 --> 00:35:11,200
And I’m not good in what way, exactly?

706
00:35:11,200 --> 00:35:14,240
You got into this place because of me.

707
00:35:14,240 --> 00:35:16,720
Oh wow, so this is what you’ve thought all along, huh, Sky?

708
00:35:16,720 --> 00:35:18,400
That I could never be as good as you?

709
00:35:19,480 --> 00:35:20,480
Exactly.

710
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:23,640
Then be amazing all by yourself. I’m done.

711
00:35:23,640 --> 00:35:24,680
What’s that supposed to mean?

712
00:35:24,680 --> 00:35:25,680
I quit.

713
00:35:27,680 --> 00:35:29,680
Wait, Chaba!

714
00:35:31,120 --> 00:35:32,760
Sky, seriously?

715
00:35:32,760 --> 00:35:35,240
Don’t fall for her act. I’ve been her friend for years.

716
00:35:35,240 --> 00:35:36,840
She’s a great actress.

717
00:35:36,840 --> 00:35:42,840
She’ll come back in one, two, three...

718
00:35:47,680 --> 00:35:48,680
She’s good.

719
00:35:50,520 --> 00:35:51,520
Four.

720
00:35:51,560 --> 00:35:52,680
Five.

721
00:35:52,680 --> 00:35:53,680
Six.

722
00:35:57,200 --> 00:35:58,200
She’s holding out this time.

723
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:00,000
Seven.

724
00:36:00,560 --> 00:36:01,560
Eight

725
00:36:02,040 --> 00:36:03,440
Nine, tada!

726
00:36:08,280 --> 00:36:10,160
Eight thousand three hundred seventy-six.

727
00:36:10,160 --> 00:36:11,720
Eight thousand three hundred seventy-seven.

728
00:36:11,720 --> 00:36:12,720
I don’t think she’s coming back.

729
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:14,000
You can stop counting now.

730
00:36:14,920 --> 00:36:16,080
No, no, the next number might bring her back.

731
00:36:16,080 --> 00:36:17,280
Don’t be ridiculous, Sky.

732
00:36:17,760 --> 00:36:20,840
No, you don’t get it. It’s a comedic beat!

733
00:36:20,840 --> 00:36:21,880
Chaba’s not coming back.

734
00:36:22,880 --> 00:36:26,240
Oh, Chai. She’s been my friend my whole life. I can tell.

735
00:36:26,240 --> 00:36:27,800
She literally handed in her resignation. Look.

736
00:36:28,040 --> 00:36:29,200
Huh?

737
00:36:51,240 --> 00:36:54,480
And that video from Ae and Laurie caused a massive booking frenzy.

738
00:36:54,480 --> 00:36:58,920
The Glamorous Airline website nearly crashed.

739
00:36:59,200 --> 00:37:00,600
People want to give it a try.

740
00:37:00,600 --> 00:37:03,680
They want to experience this magical airline at least once in their life.

741
00:37:03,680 --> 00:37:06,400
Well...I kinda wanna try it too.

742
00:37:16,080 --> 00:37:17,480
How did it end up like this?

743
00:37:17,480 --> 00:37:20,560
Madam, I know you've started going dark...

744
00:37:20,560 --> 00:37:22,120
But isn’t this a little too dark?

745
00:37:23,440 --> 00:37:25,960
This is gothic makeup.

746
00:37:30,240 --> 00:37:33,360
A black-toned look that’s both elegant and mysterious.

747
00:37:33,360 --> 00:37:34,360
Thank you.

748
00:37:35,560 --> 00:37:37,080
How did it end up like this?

749
00:37:37,480 --> 00:37:39,440
You two messed up the plan, didn’t you?

750
00:37:39,440 --> 00:37:42,440
We followed your instructions exactly, Madam. Even used your sachet.

751
00:37:42,440 --> 00:37:44,520
Then why did this happen?

752
00:37:44,520 --> 00:37:48,200
Everyone on that flight, none of them remember what happened.

753
00:37:49,360 --> 00:37:52,840
They just remember that it was...amazing.

754
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:55,880
Oh! Now I remember.

755
00:37:55,880 --> 00:37:59,280
That herb, it does drive people crazy, yes.

756
00:37:59,280 --> 00:38:03,680
But once it wears off, it makes them blissful.

757
00:38:04,560 --> 00:38:05,560
No! How could I forget?

758
00:38:05,800 --> 00:38:09,120
I tried to sabotage it...and it ended up going viral!

759
00:38:11,240 --> 00:38:13,240
Kreetha, are you...smiling?

760
00:38:14,160 --> 00:38:17,440
Uh...I guess your sachet’s effects haven’t worn off yet.

761
00:38:17,440 --> 00:38:19,680
Well then, I-I’ll just be going now, Madam.

762
00:38:19,680 --> 00:38:20,680
All-New, let’s go.

763
00:38:23,120 --> 00:38:26,680
Siri, don’t you think Kreetha’s acting a bit strange?

764
00:38:26,680 --> 00:38:28,720
No one’s stranger than you, Madam.

765
00:38:29,840 --> 00:38:33,840
I mean, I mean, no one’s as furious as you, Madam!

766
00:38:34,440 --> 00:38:37,720
The kids probably just aren’t as emotionally invested as you.

767
00:38:37,720 --> 00:38:39,680
It’s not just about being “not invested.”

768
00:38:39,960 --> 00:38:43,040
If anyone dares to betray me...

769
00:38:43,040 --> 00:38:47,040
they’ll end up just like Glamorous Airline.

770
00:38:50,040 --> 00:38:53,320
I still have plenty of tricks up my sleeve.

771
00:38:53,680 --> 00:38:54,680
Yes, Madam.

772
00:38:56,320 --> 00:39:01,000
Uh...Madam? Now that the ritual’s over, there’s nothing left, right?

773
00:39:01,240 --> 00:39:02,240
Correct.

774
00:39:02,640 --> 00:39:07,160
Then, um, can I maybe borrow that thing to take home?

775
00:39:08,360 --> 00:39:09,200
Siri!

776
00:39:09,200 --> 00:39:11,400
But I want it, Madam!

777
00:39:11,520 --> 00:39:12,520
Go home, now.

778
00:39:13,400 --> 00:39:16,760
And don’t let me find out you’re keeping it all for yourself.

779
00:39:20,640 --> 00:39:22,640
Oh no, oh no, no no!

780
00:39:23,800 --> 00:39:25,800
Oh dear God...

781
00:39:31,680 --> 00:39:35,080
There’s been a report of a missing itim...

782
00:39:35,080 --> 00:39:35,680
Excuse me.

783
00:39:35,680 --> 00:39:36,960
Missing item...

784
00:39:37,080 --> 00:39:40,160
The crew kindly asks for your cooperation as we conduct a body sash...

785
00:39:40,160 --> 00:39:41,160
search!

786
00:39:41,520 --> 00:39:43,080
Excuse me, I need to use the bathroom.

787
00:39:43,080 --> 00:39:44,080
Go, fast!

788
00:39:44,360 --> 00:39:46,040
We couldn't find the necklace.

789
00:39:46,520 --> 00:39:47,520
But we found stinky poop.

790
00:39:49,920 --> 00:39:51,440
Don't climb!

791
00:39:51,440 --> 00:39:52,360
What?

792
00:39:52,360 --> 00:39:53,120
It's correct, I said don't climb.

793
00:39:53,120 --> 00:39:54,920
Yes, and I say I'd climb.

794
00:39:54,920 --> 00:39:55,440
Right.

795
00:39:59,960 --> 00:40:00,960
Here we go!

796
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:02,200
Alright.

797
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:03,400
Hello!

798
00:40:03,400 --> 00:40:04,360
What?

799
00:40:04,360 --> 00:40:05,360
You haven't pressed the button yet.

800
00:40:07,800 --> 00:40:08,400
Hello.

801
00:40:08,400 --> 00:40:09,560
Please support us.

802
00:40:09,560 --> 00:40:10,880
Please.

803
00:40:10,880 --> 00:40:11,800
Thank you.

804
00:40:11,800 --> 00:40:13,080
Thank you for the heart me.

805
00:40:13,080 --> 00:40:14,400
Thank you for the hearts.

806
00:40:14,400 --> 00:40:15,680
It's been three hours already. Thank you.

807
00:40:15,680 --> 00:40:17,960
Three hours!

808
00:40:17,960 --> 00:40:19,840
They said it'd been three hours.

809
00:40:20,680 --> 00:40:22,600
Glamorous Airline is the absolute worst.

810
00:40:22,600 --> 00:40:23,760
The service is terrible.

811
00:40:23,760 --> 00:40:27,360
Exactly! And the...wait, what was I supposed to say? I forgot.

